SECTION 1. Any existing law to the contrary notwithstanding, the standardized salaries for bureau directors and other officials under the Department of Health are hereby fixed as follows:

Bureau Director, seventeen thousand four hundred eighty pesos

per annum

;

Chief of Offices (Field Health Operations, Administrative Services, Health Education and Personnel Training, Disease Intelligence Center and Food and Drugs Administration), sixteen thousand pesos

per annum

;

Regional Health Director, fifteen thousand four hundred eighty pesos

per annum

;

Chief of Medical Division, fifteen thousand pesos

per annum

;

Chiefs of the Jose R. Reyes Memorial Hospital (NGH), National Mental Hospital, San Lazaro Hospital, National Orthopedic Hospital, Maternity and Children's Hospital, the National Children's Hospital, and other Chiefs of designated Medical Centers and the Tala Leprosarium fifteen thousand pesos

per annum

;

Chiefs of other national hospitals, fourteen thousand five hundred pesos

per annum

;

Chief of Clinics, fourteen thousand pesos

per annum

;

;

Chiefs of other national hospitals, fourteen thousand five hundred pesos

per annum

;

Chief of Clinics, fourteen thousand pesos

per annum

;

Medical Specialist III, Medical Adviser, Chief Malariologist and Field Research Malariologist, thirteen thousand five hundred pesos

per annum

;

Medical Specialist II, Pharmacy Adviser, and Chief of Division (Non-Medical) Office of the Secretary, twelve thousand pesos

per annum

;

Hospital Department Head, and Hospital Inspector twelve thousand pesos

per annum

;

Medical Specialist I, eleven thousand pesos

per annum

;

Supervising Resident Physician, Senior Resident Physician and Senior Clinic Physician (Tuberculosis), nine thousand pesos

per annum

;

Resident Physician, and Clinic Physician, seven thousand pesos

per annum

.

Those serving on part-time basis shall receive one-half of the corresponding salaries mentioned therein.
